---
description: Use when creating or editing .cursor/rules/*.mdc to review overlap, scope rules narrowly, and avoid redundant always-apply guidance.
globs: .cursor/rules/*.mdc
alwaysApply: false
---

Before creating/updating a rule:
1. Review all files in `.cursor/rules/` to find existing matches, best fit for the change, and overlap risks.
2. Prefer updating an existing rule when responsibility is the same; create a new rule only for clearly separate responsibility.
3. Keep one concern per rule file.
4. Resolve overlap twice: before edits (structure) and after edits (dedupe/conflicts).
5. If overlap exists, explicitly merge, split responsibilities, or narrow scope so each rule has a distinct purpose.
6. Avoid duplicated guidance unless it is intentional, minimal, and justified.
7. Minimize `alwaysApply: true`; reserve it for core behavior and prefer file-scoped rules for narrow topics.
8. Keep rules short and operational; remove background text and repeated explanations.
9. Prefer referencing `.cursor/PROJECT.md` over copying project details across rules.
10. After changes, verify no conflicts, no newly redundant rules, and clear boundaries between rule files.
